values:
We have not had power since Thursday at 5 o'clock. We got power yesterday, but I was too busy running around cleaning the damn house. *laughs* Twelve people and no power for five days? Yeah, you get a bit of a mess.&nbsp;

So, now we have power again. I never realized how very much I love electricity.&nbsp;

Also, today I am going out to the tribal agency (SPIPA) and have to take part in a fashion show. *headdesk* I must also suffer high heels. Yippee. But at least I feel all nice and clean, and not like a walking greaseball. *grins* I'm dragging Justin along, too. *laughs* He keeps complaining that they all gawk at him because he's the only white kid there. In his own words, "Okay, but they all keep staring at the tall red-headed beanpole white kid, and wondering why you're going out with an Aryan." Because most of the people there look very obviously Native American. Truth be told, though, most of them could care less.&nbsp;

Other than that, my mom has a boyfriend now, has had one for two or three weeks. His name is Paul. She met him at a bar.&nbsp; She had&nbsp;not been to a bar before this for over half a dozen years, maybe a decade, I'm not sure. It's my fault she was there in&nbsp;the first place. I had stayed out all night, having called her and gotten her permission. That night she went out, got drunk, met Paul whom she says was just applying there and drank only coffee. She did not come home that night, even though she should have been there to take care of my two brothers.&nbsp;

She hasn't been home much since, and she's only slept at home maybe two or three times since she met him.&nbsp;So my uncle kicked her out. Now Mom is alternately bouncing from place to place with Paul (who has no home, no job, no anything) or sleeping in the car. She's making plans for us to move out with her, but they're really iffy. One of my brothers is really angry at her and has already refused to move out with us, which is fine, because she gave us each a choice whether to stay with my aunt and uncle or move out with her.&nbsp;I'm undecided as yet. My youngest brother is 10 years old. I raised him for the first five or six years of his life. Mom may not take care of him, if she continues like she's been doing the past few weeks. He's already decided he's moving with Mom. I'm trying to decide whether to stay here and definitely get my education, definitely be able to still see my friends and Justin, or go and make sure Sevy's going to be okay and maybe be forced to give up all that.&nbsp;

Fun, fun, fun.&nbsp;

*laughs*&nbsp;

I'm outy. I gotta go get ready for that goofy fashion show.

Yesterday the roads were iced over so bad they cancelled school. I had nothing to do all day. I cleaned my room, which hadn't been done in ages, but that only occupied my time until about 11. The rest of the day I alternately beaded and zoned out in front of the computer.&nbsp;

Today the roads were worse, but they just started school a bit late instead of cancelling it altogether. So now I am stuck here until 2 with absolutely nothing to do.&nbsp;

Blah.

I have a caffeine addiction. It's bad. Heart problems and high blood pressure run in my family. I have a cousin the same age as me who has heart arrhythmia already.&nbsp;

Justin is a smoker. This is also unhealthy, obviously.

We have struck a bargain: I will quit the caffeine if he will quit the nicotine. He's quite happy with the deal, possibly because I've been insanely hyper in class the last couple of days. And I am happy with the deal, and if he does not quit by his 19th birthday (this December) like he promised, I will ruin his cigarettes. *grins* It's a good deal.&nbsp;

In other news: no love, Washington. No love at all. Rain for a week in a row and temperatures that would make a well-digger shiver? No. Just no.

Got into college for the fall quarter.&nbsp;I'm taking Art, Psychology, and Life and Career Planning this quarter. Next quarter I'm taking Tai Chi, too, but this quarter it was full.&nbsp;

Wrote another song. I also wrote a short X-men pseudo-slash fic I want Kage to come beta for me. Because she's good like that.&nbsp;

I went to the fair twice this weekend and had sooooo much fun. I only went on a few rides (I get motion-sick, not to the point of throwing up, but enough that it's rather off-putting), but the atmosphere is just awesome. I love it. The noise, the crowds, the people, the grins everywhere, the lights and colors and shiny stuff everywhere, the music, the noise, did I mention the noise? Mom pretty much had to pry me off the ceiling both times when we got home, but it was awesome. I played some games, won my youngest brother two pimp hats (one of which has a Jolly Roger and says Booty Call and God it's great that he wears it without knowing what "booty call" is), and had an elephant ear and cotton candy and a caramel apple.&nbsp;I bought a really cute skirt from this little old Chinese lady, too. She was about to close her booth and since it was closing time she left off the tax for me. I also got a temporary Batsignal tattoo that Kage needs to see because she will squee.&nbsp;

*grins* Well, I need to go help clean the house, and my brother is earning his nickname (Sarge) while we're at it, so I'm gonna leave the other stuff I wanted to say for later.
